<title>UK: Conrad CEO will resign after Sheffield deal.</title>
<headline>Conrad CEO will resign after Sheffield deal.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The chief executive of Conrad Plc, the UK leisure group which is in talks with Sheffield United Football Club about a possible takeover, said he would resign from his post after the deal is clinched.</p>
<p>Michael Edelson, Conrad chief executive, told Reuters: &quot;When the deal is completed, because I am a director of Manchester United (football club) which is my first love, I will be resigning from Conrad.&quot;</p>
<p>Before joining Conrad, Edelson worked for his family business. His possible successor will be Charles Green, chief executive of Sheffield United football club.</p>
<p>--Edna Fernandes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
